org.smooks.api

Interface TypedMap

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    ExecutionContext
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultExecutionContext

    public interface TypedMap
    AttributeStore interface definition.

    Defines methods for binding, getting and removing named objects on an implementing class.

    Author:
    tfennelly

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      <T> T get(TypedKey<T> key)
      Returns the object bound with the specified name in this TypedMap implementation, or null if no object is bound under the name.
      Map<TypedKey<Object>,Object> getAll()
      Returns the Map of attributes bound in this TypedMap

    • Method Detail

      • put

        <T> void put(TypedKey<T> key,
             T value)
        Binds an object to this TypedMap implementation, using the name specified. If an object of the same name is already bound, the object is replaced.

        Parameters:
        key - The key against which the object is bound; cannot be null.
        value - The object to be bound; cannot be null.

      • get

        <T> T get(TypedKey<T> key)
        Returns the object bound with the specified name in this TypedMap implementation, or null if no object is bound under the name.
        Parameters:
        key - The key against which the object is bound; cannot be null.
        Returns:
        The object bound with the specified name in this TypedMap implementation, or null if no object is bound under the name.

      • getOrDefault

        <T> T getOrDefault(TypedKey<T> key,
                   T value)

      • getAll

        Map<TypedKey<Object>,Object> getAll()
        Returns the Map of attributes bound in this TypedMap
        Returns:
        Map of all objects bound in this TypedMap

      • remove

        <T> void remove(TypedKey<T> key)
        Removes the object bound with the specified name from this TypedMap implementation. If the TypedMap implementation does not have an object bound with the specified name, this method does nothing.
        Parameters:
        key - The key against which the object is bound; cannot be null.
